. </p>\n<p id=\"nrnbuk\">\u201cThe short answer is no,\u201d Ola K\u00e4llenius told <em>The Verge</em>\u2019s Nilay Patel in response to a question about whether Mercedes-Benz will enable Apple CarPlay to take over all the screens inside its", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/29/24144356/mercedes-benz-ceo-apple-carplay-next-gen-decoder", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Mercedes-Benz won\u2019t let Apple CarPlay take over all its screens", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-29T14:44:07+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Pixel Watch 2 with its screen on, next to the original Pixel Watch with its screen off.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tlu14jiNBGBAoxi4TC7WY193aGk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73315133/236828_Pixel_Watch_2_AKrales_0705.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>If you\u2019re not a Samsung user, this is the best Android smartwatch you can buy.</em> | Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"BAZc8D\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/14/24101171/google-io-2024-announced-may-14-android-ai-gemini\">Google I/O</a> is right around the corner, and if history repeats itself, the company will likely use its annual keynote to announce new software features across all of its various platforms, including Android, Chrome, and Search. Google also sometimes brings a surprise device announcement to the party, but we wouldn\u2019t bet on a new flagship smartwatch considering the <a href=\"https://www.th", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/29/24144248/google-pixel-watch-2-xbox-game-pass-ultimate-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google\u2019s Pixel Watch 2 is matching its lowest price with $50 off", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-29T14:40:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage of Mercedes CEO Ola K\u00e4llenius.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/zeCXeOzeQgzN5nupSrR3rDXuIlQ=/1x0:2760x1839/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73315122/decoder.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo illustration by The Verge / Photo: Mercedes-Benz</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The all-EV future might not land in 2030, but it\u2019s coming \u2014 and a new slate of challenges is coming with it.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24140551/mercedes-benz-ola-kallenius-ev-gwagen-carplay-apple\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24140551/mercedes-benz-ola-kallenius-ev-gwagen-carplay-apple", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Mercedes-Benz CEO Ola K\u00e4llenius on not using Apple\u2019s next-gen CarPlay and why EVs are still the future", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-29T14:30:00+00:00", "description": "<p>Their small variations in design make a big difference.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24140334/asus-zenbook-duo-vs-lenovo-yoga-book-9i\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24140334/asus-zenbook-duo-vs-lenovo-yoga-book-9i", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Duel of the dual-screen laptops: Asus Zenbook Duo vs. Lenovo Yoga Book 9i", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-29T14:21:07+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing Elon Musk on a background with hammers\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/pkFkyqrcazQ77QhdWRLmfx5uHbA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73315062/STK171_VRG_Illo_5_Normand_ElonMusk_05.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Laura Normand / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"1MUOa6\">Elon Musk\u2019s efforts to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/5/15/23723969/elon-musk-twitter-sitter-sec-settlement-court-reject\">nullify a settlement</a> with the Securities and Exchange Commission that requires him to get a lawyer\u2019s preapproval for some posts related to Tesla has been <a href=\"https://www.supremecourt.gov/orders/courtorders/042924zor_ihdj.pdf\">rejected by the US Supreme Court</a>. </p>\n<p id=\"cfs1hi\">Musk has been required to receive approval from his so-called \u201cTwitter sitter\u201d after signing a consent decree with the SEC in 2018 in response to his tweets about taking Tesla private, in which he f", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/29/24144317/elon-musk-supreme-court-twitter-sitter-sec-tesla", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Supreme Court rejects Elon Musk\u2019s efforts to get rid of his \u2018Twitter sitter\u2019", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-29T13:40:44+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The driver screen seen through the steering wheel in a Mach-E, the screen says \u201chands-free\u201d\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_vhLnPXVoaKu9P5k5v6qr_yrNlQ=/0x0:3318x2212/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73314950/IMG_0859.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>A Mustang Mach-E running Ford\u2019s hands-free software.</em> | Image: Umar Shakir / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"3dZjBn\">The National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA) has opened an official investigation into Ford\u2019s BlueCruise advanced driver-assistance software after it\u2019s been linked to multiple fatalities while in use. <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/12/24128349/ford-hands-free-bluecruise-fatal-crash-texas-ntsb\">It includes two 2024 incidents</a> that the National Transportation Safety Board is also investigating \u2014 one in San Antonio and another in Philadelphia.</p>\n<p id=\"2wXOgD\">The NHTSA\u2019s Office of Defects Investigation <a href=\"https://www.docu", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/29/24144244/nhtsa-ford-bluecruise-software-investigation-fatal-crashes-mustang-mach-e", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "NHTSA opens investigation into Ford\u2019s BlueCruise after software linked to fatal crash", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-29T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage of the TikTok logo over a photograph of the US Capitol building.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/beRYAET_D1v6MPyNFTUuzS-DeZM=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73314656/STK051_TIKTOKBAN2_CVirginia_C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photo from Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Having lost its fight in Congress, TikTok faces a tough battle in US courts\u00a0and with China\u2019s own export controls. </p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24141539/tiktok-ban-bytedance-china-dc-circuit-supreme-court\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24141539/tiktok-ban-bytedance-china-dc-circuit-supreme-court", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The legal challenges that lie ahead for TikTok \u2014 in both the US and China", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-29T11:44:47+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"12.9-inch iPad Pro running Final Cut Pro\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/58pGpxvRh26LyJleS8zsxaC4TK8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73314643/DSCF4643.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>iOS, Safari, and the App Store were already designated as Gatekeeper services under the DMA in September 2023.</em> | Photo by Vjeran Pavic / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"vRCMbl\">Following an almost eight-month investigation into whether Apple\u2019s iPadOS holds enough market power to warrant stricter regulation, the European Commission has now designated the iPad operating system as a Gatekeeper service under its flagship <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24040543/eu-dma-digital-markets-act-big-tech-antitrust\">Digital Markets Act (DMA)</a> rules.</p>\n<p id=\"1HXyxu\">\u201cThe Commission concluded that iPadOS constitutes an important gateway for business users to reach end users, and that Apple enjoys an entrenched and durable pos", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/29/24144209/ipados-ipad-eu-commission-dma-rules-compliance-regulation", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "iPads join iPhones in requirement to follow strict EU rules", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-29T09:52:49+00:00", "description": "<p>\u2018The world\u2019s lightest city e-bike\u2019 claim is worth a test, if not your $1,799.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24144163/fiido-air-carbon-fiber-e-bike-review-price-specs\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24144163/fiido-air-carbon-fiber-e-bike-review-price-specs", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Fiido Air review: so lightweight you\u2019ll forget it\u2019s an e-bike", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-29T08:15:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage of a computer with the ChatGPT logo on the screen.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/acNt441r4SBgbVpq-oOIyQB0Gck=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73314450/STK_414_AI_CHATBOT_R2_CVirginia_B.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos by Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"jx4LZn\">The <em>Financial Times</em> has struck a deal with OpenAI to license its content and develop AI tools, the latest news organization to work with the AI company. </p>\n<p id=\"H2Cl0O\">The <em>FT</em> writes in a press release that ChatGPT users will see summaries, quotes, and links to its articles. Any prompt that returns information from the <em>FT</em> will be attributed to the publication. </p>\n<p id=\"gJyQfR\">In return, OpenAI will work with the news organization to develop new AI products. The <em>FT</em> already uses OpenAI products, saying it is a customer of ChatGPT Enterprise. L", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/29/24141869/financial-times-licensing-deal-openai-news", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Financial Times signs licensing deal with OpenAI", "user": null, "vote": 0}]